Nagios-Poller

Nagios::Poller is a host-side monitoring daemon that schedules and runs
check plugins locally and submits check results to one or more Nagios
parent servers via NSCA.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Nagios::Poller

There is a man page for the npoll utility as well.

    man npoll

